It&#x27;s suboptimal and obscure. There is barely any up to date resources on it.<p>So far I&#x27;ve managed to get to stuff presented on the window, but as soon as you start messing with references to the DOM components, things start to break down.<p>It&#x27;s a shame, I really think Typescript and React would be the answer to getting a decent code base.<p>One of the cool parts, is that you get to define what your property is with static type checking and have no need to use Reacts on PropValidator.<p>let search = new SearchBox<{
                            options:SearchOptions, 
                            onSearch:OnSearchHandler>
                            })<p>That tells you that the SearchBox props contains SearchOptions and a delegate to call when searching<p>I&#x27;m just starting with both React and TypeScript, so it could just be me.
